		{"id":"b1807561fff243b6","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nrpc_method = ident `(` ident `)` `:` ident metadata `;`\n```","x":4860,"y":2500,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"9a0c12f354c640f0","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- ","x":4860,"y":2600,"width":580,"height":100},
		{"id":"9d218816b72ee5f7","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nobject = `{` commasep(ident`:`value) `}`\n```","x":5540,"y":2300,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"96ab484020fb2321","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- I don't know when this is used. Needs more research before I go and implement anything for it.","x":5540,"y":2400,"width":580,"height":100},
		{"id":"4ef892f989720e40","type":"text","text":"- [ ] empty object = `{fbs} {}`\n- [ ] single_value = `{fbs} {ident:value}`\n    - [ ] int dec/hex = `{fbs} {ident:1}`, `{fbs} {ident:0xA}`\n    - [ ] float dec/hex = `{fbs} {ident:1.0}`, `{fbs} {ident:0x0.F}`\n    - [ ] string = `{fbs} {ident:\"value\"}`\n- [ ] multi-value = `{fbs} {ident1:value,ident2:value}`\n- [ ] array value = `{fbs} {ident:[value1,value2]}`\n- [ ] nested object = `{fbs} {ident:{ident:value}}`\n- [ ] array nested = `{fbs} {ident:[{ident:value}]}`\n- [ ] nested array = `{fbs} {ident:{ident:[value]}}`","x":5540,"y":2520,"width":580,"height":300},
		{"id":"6cd3213c4c27200b","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nenum_decl = `enum` ident `:` type metadata `{`\n    commasep(ident [`=` integer_constant] metadata)\n`}`\n```","x":700,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"13a3ec09ddb2967f","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- Godot enums can only be integers, so allowing the type to be anything other than an integer type makes no sense in this context.\n- Godot has two types of enums: named, and unnamed. I wonder if it is worth creating an attribute to enable generation alternatives\n- I can see a need for an attribute to specify that the enum is included from an external type, or file. Or that the values are globally available","x":700,"y":1760,"width":580,"height":280},
		{"id":"d1a0c2e8bf2d53aa","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nroot_decl = `root_type` ident `;`\n```","x":20,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"e873bac88d44b71d","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- ","x":20,"y":1720,"width":580,"height":100},
		{"id":"c47c79fceff0ea8e","type":"text","text":"- [ ] standard root decl\n- [ ] no root\n- [ ] root from included type\n- [ ] arbitrary root with cmdline flag","x":20,"y":1840,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"cf8938bf54a8e8c9","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nattribute_decl = `attribute` ident | `\"` ident `\"` `;`\n```","x":20,"y":2100,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"5f4314da7bc7a946","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- We need to forward declare custom attributes that we wish to use in the schema I think, more testing is required.","x":20,"y":2200,"width":580,"height":140},
		{"id":"344deafbeead6a96","type":"text","text":"- [ ] enum declaration\n    - [ ] syntax error on using a non integer type\n    - [ ] attribute for unnamed alias?\n    - [ ] allow alternate types for a constant dictionary if\n          attribute? or automatic?\n- [ ] enum value\n    - [ ] ?","x":700,"y":2060,"width":580,"height":200},
		{"id":"b37498ae54c1cb2c","type":"text","text":"- [ ] Wanted Custom Attributes\n    - [ ] @tool - mark generated script as tool","x":20,"y":2360,"width":580,"height":100},
		{"id":"3f904f875f6b6d3c","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nnamespace_decl = `namespace` ident(`.`ident)* `;`\n```","x":700,"y":2600,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"7838b325eb1a543d","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nfile_extension_decl = `file_extension` string_constant `;`\n```","x":-660,"y":2640,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"061e21ac0fdd202e","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nfile_identifier_decl = `file_identifier` string_constant `;`\n```","x":20,"y":2640,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"c0949af83cf081b4","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- ?","x":-660,"y":2740,"width":580,"height":80},
