		{"id":"8d912e081e33ee03","type":"text","text":"**Notes:**\n- It's not clear to me if or how namespaces could be used in gdscript.","x":700,"y":2700,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"77972ad80364ab93","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\ninclude = `include` string_constant `;`\n```","x":-660,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"3739a14f1326577b","type":"text","text":"- [ ] Testing of includes would involve testing all features from an included file\n- [ ] multiple layers of include\n- Absolute Paths\n    - [ ] `{c} \"/path\"`\n    - [ ] `{c} \"C:/path\"`\n- Relative Paths \n    - [ ] `{c} \"./relative/path\"`\n    - [ ] `{c} \"relative/path\"`\n- Godot Paths\n    - [ ] `{c} \"res://path\"`\n    - [ ] `{c} \"user://path\"`\n- Special Cases\n    - [ ] `{c} \"godot.fbs\"`\n- [ ] Path separators `\"/\"` or `\"\\\"`","x":-660,"y":1720,"width":580,"height":440},
		{"id":"026e23444fa360c8","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nunion_decl = `union` ident metadata `{`\n    commasep(ident [`=` ident] metadata)\n`}`\n```","x":1380,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"629c918a2125ea6d","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- ","x":1380,"y":1760,"width":580,"height":160},
		{"id":"5e2aa5fca7527c16","type":"text","text":"- [ ] union members\n    - [ ] aliased union\n    - [ ] native type attribute\n    - [ ] syntax error on alias collision","x":1380,"y":1940,"width":580,"height":320},
		{"id":"b4f5930fc6d7e45c","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\ndoc_comments = `///` anything\n```","x":1400,"y":2600,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"c92086d43ed2317d","type":"text","text":"**Notes:**\n- Documentation comments need to be re-produced in the output.","x":1400,"y":2700,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"4cbe0212a7675105","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\ntable_decl = `table` ident [metadata] `{`\n    field_decl+\n`}`\n```","x":2060,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"ae1e26cb0c54830f","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- ","x":2060,"y":1760,"width":580,"height":160},
		{"id":"461a13d5e9ddac0b","type":"text","text":"- [ ] object-api with metadata: `(native:ident)`\n- [ ] empty table\n- [ ] inline field types\n    - [ ] scalar values\n    - [ ] struct\n    - [ ] array\n- [ ] offset field types\n    - [ ] table\n    - [ ] union\n    - [ ] vector","x":2060,"y":1940,"width":580,"height":320},
		{"id":"4593e17cb670624f","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nstruct_decl = `struct` ident [metadata] `{`\n    field_decl+\n`}`\n```","x":2720,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":120},
		{"id":"d0eef5c658b3a60e","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- structs are stored inline, this restricts the types that can be represented\n- Godot doesn't have a concept of structs, but some variant types are under the hood and can be used as such","x":2720,"y":1760,"width":580,"height":200},
		{"id":"57eec75def1119ca","type":"text","text":"- [ ] empty struct is a failure\n- [ ] inline types\n    - [ ] struct\n    - [ ] scalars / enums\n    - [ ] appropriate godot types like vector3\n    - [ ] fixed arrays","x":2720,"y":1980,"width":580,"height":260},
		{"id":"f7416cdfd5602bc0","type":"text","text":"```ebnf\nfield_decl = ident `:` type [`=` scalar] [metadata] `;`\n```","x":3420,"y":1620,"width":580,"height":80},
		{"id":"3835f4a6fe4f2c22","type":"text","text":"**Notes**\n- For tables and structs I need to test the expression of fields.","x":3420,"y":1720,"width":580,"height":160},
		{"id":"e670e9d40c6a0805","type":"text","text":"- Type Categories\n    - [ ] scalar\n    - [ ] vector\n    - [ ] fixed array\n    - [ ] table\n    - [ ] struct\n    - [ ] union","x":3420,"y":2020,"width":580,"height":220}
